# CODEOWNERS - Automatic Review Request Configuration
#
# IMPORTANT: This is an EXAMPLE file. Before activating:
# 1. Replace ALL "@your-org/..." placeholders with actual GitHub usernames or team names
# 2. Verify all teams exist in your organization settings
# 3. Test with a draft PR to ensure proper assignment
# 4. Invalid references will cause GitHub to silently ignore CODEOWNERS rules
#
# To activate this file:
# 1. Review and update all placeholder values below
# 2. Rename this file to "CODEOWNERS" (without .example)
# 3. Commit and push to your repository
#
# When a PR modifies files matching these patterns, GitHub will automatically
# request review from the specified users or teams.
#
# Integration with Spec-Kit Workflows:
# - Use this to ensure appropriate reviewers are assigned based on workflow type
# - Combine with spec-kit review enforcement for comprehensive quality control
# - Teams/users will be notified to perform human review after /speckit.review
#
# Syntax:
# pattern @username @org/team-name
#
# More info: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# ==============================================================================
# Default Owners (Fallback)
# ==============================================================================

# Default owners for everything in the repo (unless a more specific rule below)
# *       @your-org/engineering-team

# ==============================================================================
# Spec-Kit Workflow Directories
# ==============================================================================

# All spec-kit specifications (any workflow type)
specs/                          @your-org/tech-leads

# Feature specifications
specs/[0-9][0-9][0-9]-*/       @your-org/product-team @your-org/engineering-leads

# ==============================================================================
# Bug Fix Workflows
# ==============================================================================

# Bug fix specifications and implementations
specs/bugfix/                   @your-org/qa-team @your-org/senior-engineers

# Critical bug fixes (hotfix workflow)
specs/hotfix/                   @your-org/engineering-leads @your-org/tech-leads

# ==============================================================================
# Enhancement and Modification Workflows
# ==============================================================================

# Enhancement specifications
specs/enhance/                  @your-org/product-team

# Modification specifications (changes to existing features)
specs/modify/                   @your-org/product-team @your-org/architecture-team

# ==============================================================================
# Code Quality Workflows
# ==============================================================================

# Refactoring work
specs/refactor/                 @your-org/senior-engineers @your-org/architecture-team

# Code cleanup
specs/cleanup/                  @your-org/senior-engineers

# ==============================================================================
# Deprecation and Baseline Workflows
# ==============================================================================

# Feature deprecation (impacts users)
specs/deprecate/                @your-org/product-team @your-org/engineering-leads

# Baseline documentation
specs/baseline/                 @your-org/tech-writers @your-org/documentation-team

# ==============================================================================
# Source Code by Technology/Component
# ==============================================================================

# Frontend code
src/components/                 @your-org/frontend-team
src/pages/                      @your-org/frontend-team
*.tsx                          @your-org/frontend-team
