# ==============================================================================
# Integration with Spec-Kit Review Workflow
# ==============================================================================

# How CODEOWNERS works with spec-kit review:
#
# 1. Developer completes implementation
# 2. Developer runs: /speckit.review (AI code review)
# 3. Review file generated with findings
# 4. Developer commits review file
# 5. Developer creates PR
# 6. GitHub automatically requests human reviewers (via CODEOWNERS)
# 7. Automated workflow checks for approved review file
# 8. Human reviewers perform additional review
# 9. Both AI review (approved) + human review (approved) required to merge
#
# This creates a comprehensive review process:
# - AI Review (/speckit.review): Fast, consistent, catches common issues
# - Human Review (CODEOWNERS): Context-aware, architectural decisions, UX
# - Automated Enforcement (GitHub Actions): Ensures process is followed

# ==============================================================================
# Customization Instructions
# ==============================================================================

# To use this file:
# 1. Rename: CODEOWNERS.example → CODEOWNERS
# 2. Replace @your-org/team-name with your actual GitHub org and team names
# 3. Replace @username with actual GitHub usernames
# 4. Customize patterns to match your project structure
# 5. Commit to .github/CODEOWNERS
# 6. Enable branch protection requiring reviews
#
# Tips:
# - Start simple, add complexity as needed
# - Use teams rather than individuals for flexibility
# - More specific rules override general rules
# - Use wildcards (*) for pattern matching
# - Test with a draft PR to verify correct reviewers assigned
#
# Advanced: Require different numbers of reviewers
# - Set in: Settings → Branches → Branch protection rules
# - Require X number of approving reviews
# - Dismiss stale reviews when new commits pushed
# - Require review from code owners
